{"word":"ἐγκύκλιος","slug":"ἐγκύκλιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐγκύκλιος</b></el> <el>(ἐγ-κύκλιος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κύκλος'><el>κύκλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>circular, rounded, round</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>revolving in a cycle, periodical</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:— <i>ordinary</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>quotidianus</el>, <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}